---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import InteractiveChecker from '../components/InteractiveChecker.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="SMS Scam Checker - Phishing Text Scanner - TrustChecker"
  description="Identify package delivery frauds (USPS/FedEx), banking security alarms, and prize shortlink tricks inside text messages. Scan text messages for free."
  activePath="/sms-scam-checker"
>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-10">
    <!-- Header -->
    <header class="text-center flex flex-col items-center gap-4 select-none">
      <span class="caption-mono text-link font-semibold">SMISHING ANALYSIS</span>
      <h1 class="display-lg text-ink font-semibold">SMS scam checker.</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-body max-w-lg">
        Determine if a text message is a phishing attempt. Paste package tracking messages, bank notifications, or crypto links below to check credibility.
      </p>
    </header>

    <!-- Checker Dashboard -->
    <InteractiveChecker defaultTab="sms" />

    <!-- Educational section -->
    <section class="border-t border-hairline pt-10 select-none flex flex-col gap-6">
      <h2 class="display-sm text-ink">Spotting common SMS text scams.</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 text-xs text-body leading-relaxed">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1">
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">1. Package Delivery Redirection (USPS/FedEx)</span>
          <p>
            Scammers send messages claiming "Your package cannot be delivered due to an incorrect house number. Please update details at this link." The shortlink goes to a clone site that asks for custom fees ($1.50) to steel credit card info.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1">
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">2. Fake Bank Security Suspensions</span>
          <p>
            Alerts stating "Chase Alert: Suspicious transaction detected. Account locked. Confirm identity immediately" contain links to credential-harvesting pages. Bank companies never send alerts from personal 10-digit mobile lines.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1">
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">3. Obscured URL Shortlinks</span>
          <p>
            Phishing links frequently use custom redirects (like `tinyurl.com/`, `bit.ly/`, or random names like `usps-redelivery-postal.xyz`) instead of the official company domains. Never tap a shortened link.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-4 bg-canvas border border-hairline rounded shadow-level1">
          <span class="font-semibold text-ink">4. Unsolicited Sweepstakes & Refunds</span>
          <p>
            Messages claiming you have won a $500 Walmart gift card or are owed a refund from your utility provider are bait. Legitimate payouts are never delivered via unsolicited mobile text links.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>
